Indoor/Outdoor Usage

  • Human/Vehicle Detection: This IP camera is equipped with on-device detection technology to identify human and vehicles from other objects. With its accurate detection, you can keep a sharper eye on the true threats and release your mind from the unnecessary alerts.
  • 4K Ultra HD Videos: The home security camera jumps from 5MP to 4K Ultra HD. It is 1.6X clearer than 5MP and 4X clearer than 1080p. Details you see around home or store will be reproduced perfectly in live streaming and playback. Audio recording helps to record the ambient sound for more details.
  • Easy PoE Installation: Thanks to the power over Ethernet (PoE) technology, this outdoor camera can transmit videos and get power simultaneously via only one network cable. Easy plug-and-play for a reliable connection.
  • Multiple Recording Options: The PoE cam supports to record 24/7 continuously when movement is detected or during scheduled time. Videos can be saved in the micro SD card (up to 256GB, NOT included), Reolink NVR or FTP server.
  • Real-Time Motion Alerts: Whenever the danger is detected, this surveillance camera will trigger alerts by sending real-time push notifications or alert emails to your device. You can watch live feed, be informed of the emergency, replay key moments - all can be done on Reolink App or Client anytime and anywhere.

Product description

This RLC-820A security camera comes with keen and sharp 4K 'eyes' that can understand what it sees by the leading-edge human/vehicle detection. Unnecessary alerts from disturbing factors such as waving leaves, flying bugs, moving shadows will be reduced greatly. Enjoy peace of mind with this smart home security assistant.


Flexible Recording Options

This security camera can optionally record motions events or 24/7 to a microSD card (Up to 256GB, not included), Reolink NVR, or FTP server. More space provided by the microSD card, longer footage can be saved from this camera under default bitrate in 24/7 recording schedule.


Remote Access Anytime & Anywhere

Feel free to Live view and share the fun moments with your family or friends via Reolink App/Client wherever you are. The camera supports up to 12 users using different devices to live stream simultaneously (with 2 mainstreams & 10 substreams).


Outstanding 4K@25fps UHD Videos

This outdoor PoE camera shoots 4K high-quality videos at 25fps, delivering an unparalleled smoother and clearer viewing experience than ever. Details you see around home or store will be recorded perfectly in live streaming and playback, no matter day or night.


Visualize the Passing of Time

The time-lapse function allows you to capture the dynamic processes vividly and visually, such as the sunrise or sunset, flowers blossom, and the construction of a building, then watches the whole process in minutes and seconds. (Time-lapse only works on Reolink App.)


Work With Smart Home

Get the camera to join your smart home! Just tell your device to show you the camera, and you will see live feed on your Chromecast-enabled TVs. Action speaks louder than words? No, words are enough. Moreover, no extra subscription or charges will be needed.


IP66 Waterproof for Outdoor Use

With the rugged housing and body, this security camera can keep guard anywhere, outdoors or indoors, and in any harsh weather conditions.

  • Temperature: -10°C - +55°C (14°F - 131°F)
  • Humidity: 10% - 90%

FAQ

  • Question 1: How to get the camera working?
  • Answer: With the power from IEEE802.3af PoE switch/injector (NOT included) via one CAT5,6, or 7 ethernet cable (up to 330ft, one 1m/3.3ft cable included), you could set up and access the camera via Reolink App, Reolink PC client, or web browser (Edge, Chrome, Firefox, Safari).
  • Question 2: Will this work with the Reolink NVR or system?
  • Answer: Yes, it does. Reolink NVRs with the hardware version of N7MB01/N6MB01/N5MB01/H3MB18/N3MB01/N2MB02 under the latest firmware version support the smart detection/playback for the RLC-820A. You can verify the compatibility via the System Information of the NVR.
  • Question 3: Is the camera compatible with third-party software/System/NVR?
  • Answer: The RLC-820A IP camera can be added to some third-party software/NVR such as Blus Iris or Synology. But currently, we could only ensure the full compatibility between this camera and the Reolink NVR/software.

    • DJC
      5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Good picture and person/vehicle detection (motion not so much)
      Reviewed in the United States on February 18, 2022
      Color: White
      The picture quality is good. Not great, it can't possibly be with the 8Mbps stream bandwidth at 8MP resolution. It can be used stand-alone or connected to a NVR; standalone can record on an SD card or store on a FTP server. The person/vehicle detection works... See more
      The picture quality is good. Not great, it can't possibly be with the 8Mbps stream bandwidth at 8MP resolution.
      It can be used stand-alone or connected to a NVR; standalone can record on an SD card or store on a FTP server.
      The person/vehicle detection works great if you tweak the parameters a bit for minimum/maximum size plus duration. Motion detection is useless unless you place it indoors - too sensitive or too insensitive.
      There are severe compression artifacts with only 8Mbps bandwidth - to the point where you'd wonder if it's 8MP or just an upscaled 2MP sensor, but it's a security camera, not one for wining an Oscar.
      Night vision is good to about 60ft realistically. If there is a real floodlight to assist then the image is quite good. Even moonlight helps at greater distances.
      Push notifications are a bit annoying, going as often as 30sec and there is no picture or app deeplink to play from the event attached to the notification, all you can do is go to the live view. Emailed pictures for events on the other side are spot on (for person/vehicle).
      Some features are lost if you connect the camera to the monitoring ports of the Reolink NVR, but if you have it on the LAN side you can access them (such as pet detection) via the app.
      In all not bad given the price, features and image quality, plus it works seamlessly with the Reolink NVR.

      UPDATE: The Reolink team offered me a discount on my next purchase for the lack of sFTP support. Fair enough, until having agreed a small percentage discount and bought another camera they WELCHED on the discount. Nice going Reolink. Expect customer service with a smile, a promise and … ZERO FOLLOW THROUGH.

      Original post:
      Set up and operation was a dream. Working within minutes. Good pictures to my phone and pc without any complex set up. Microphone is clear.

      Two gripes: The movement detection is trigger happy. Rain, bugs, birds all trigger a recording even with settings on low sensitivity. Min detection size doesn’t prevent a bug shooting across the field of view triggering. In one night I had 36 emails. It was raining. So unless you’re keen to review hours of footage then you’ll end up turning off notifications. But I bought it for the view not security so not a problem.

      The second issue is that the camera can’t upload footage to a web host (for remote storage) using sFTP. This means that your footage can be intercepted/hacked. Probably not an issue to most people but a surprising omission. The support team have been responsive but I await a solution.

    • # ʕっ•ᴥ•ʔっ ~ ~ ~
      1.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Poor viewing angles when used as a porch camera
      Reviewed in the United States on March 4, 2024
      Color: White
      Unfortunately, this camera does not make the cut when installed as a porch camera pointed *inwards* from the outside (and mounted on the ceiling). The viewing angle needs to be wider to capture a good picture, and the camera is zoomed in quite heavily on the vertical side.... See more
      Unfortunately, this camera does not make the cut when installed as a porch camera pointed *inwards* from the outside (and mounted on the ceiling). The viewing angle needs to be wider to capture a good picture, and the camera is zoomed in quite heavily on the vertical side. Because of that, you have to compromise with what you have:

      1. Point the camera downwards, and capture the ground so you can look for delivered packages, but miss the faces of people coming and going since it's mainly staring at the ground.
      or
      2. Point the camera higher up and capture partially the door and some faces, but miss the ground completely so you have no idea if packages are still there.
      or
      3. Rotate the camera sideways so the camera captures more of the vertical space in exchange for a much narrower horizontal view. This allows much more of the desired areas to be recorded, albeit sideways.

      While option 3 seems like a good compromise, neither the app nor the website allows you to flip the image so any recording you make will be permanently sideways. You will be tilting your head to view recordings made in this way. The app might be easier since you can physically rotate your phone, but it still is pretty annoying. The sideways recording also seems to affect the ability of its AI to detect people, therefore causing some interesting events to be missed.

      Furthermore, it doesn't seem like the company has any plans to fix this problem (now or in the future), instead opting to give me a discount on a new camera if I wanted to buy something new from them. This is quite frustrating given that this is still a relatively new camera and it is still being actively sold.

      This camera may be acceptable if you are just looking to point it out on the street to get general details, but you probably will be disappointed if you are using it for specific use cases like confirming package deliveries.
      One person found this helpful
